1,0.089338,0.085915,0.083872,0.077402,0.071708],"unified_progress":[0.054808,0.078347,0.08362,0.089126,0.092265,0.095436,0.094158,0.095595,0.090177,0.085698,0.076037,0.064733]},{"section":5,"text":"The locations\u2014knees, elbows, upper back, and buttocks\u2014suggest a systemic rather than localized issue.","dimension":9,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.058922,0.085157,0.087509,0.089871,0.086247,0.086771,0.089102,0.087223,0.085011,0.08359,0.082003,0.078595],"unified_progress":[0.059777,0.07907,0.081255,0.085056,0.087302,0.090691,0.089148,0.09385,0.091066,0.087477,0.081569,0.07374]},{"section":6,"text":"I recall that in bullous pemphigoid, IgA is deposited at the dermoepidermal junction, which is exactly what the DIF shows here.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037201,0.056758,0.070632,0.082725,0.092119,0.09756,0.10133,0.10209,0.10013,0.093431,0.084315,0.08172],"unified_progress":[0.032758,0.056709,0.0802,0.088896,0.094301,0.10374,0.10099,0.098023,0.096559,0.09332,0.08194,0.072562]},{"section":7,"text":"Bullous pemphigoid is a type of blistering disease that affects the skin and can present with these types of lesions.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.01876,0.038087,0.056986,0.071503,0.092892,0.10532,0.11256,0.12135,0.11991,0.10329,0.083527,0.075821],"unified_progress":[0.022205,0.047863,0.072722,0.089498,0.097608,0.11522,0.11105,0.10866,0.10271,0.097212,0.076272,0.058985]},{"section":8,"text":"The fact that the IgA is also found in the dermal papilla might support this diagnosis as well.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043692,0.046067,0.05826,0.068942,0.078115,0.085842,0.09238,0.097046,0.10016,0.10253,0.10736,0.11961],"unified_progress":[0.03899,0.050721,0.063073,0.074303,0.082151,0.090293,0.090832,0.097226,0.099161,0.098622,0.10459,0.11003]},{"section":9,"text":"Other possibilities could include pemphigus vulgaris, but that typically involves IgG deposits, not IgA. Dermatitis, like atopic or contact, usually doesn't show IgA deposits on DIF.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.021941,0.040238,0.058841,0.070595,0.083983,0.094548,0.1025,0.11194,0.11645,0.11307,0.10221,0.083693],"unified_progress":[0.025016,0.049581,0.069318,0.081351,0.090815,0.10027,0.10302,0.10615,0.10607,0.10746,0.091157,0.069797]},{"section":10,"text":"Scleroderma can have skin changes, but it's more about fibrosis and not specifically IgA deposition in these areas.","dimension":5,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.021387,0.037398,0.056187,0.069298,0.083566,0.096069,0.10476,0.1165,0.12086,0.11539,0.10346,0.075127],"unified_progress":[0.024078,0.047242,0.066636,0.080239,0.091669,0.10111,0.10534,0.11085,0.11,0.11393,0.089705,0.059194]},{"section":11,"text":"So, putting it all together, the presence of IgA at the dermoepidermal junction and dermal papilla, along with the distribution of the lesions, points towards bullous pemphigoid as the most likely diagnosis.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.014352,0.024391,0.031595,0.038195,0.044028,0.051932,0.061233,0.076395,0.094644,0.1201,0.17113,0.272],"unified_progress":[0.013882,0.024698,0.032362,0.042475,0.048326,0.063633,0.067665,0.083673,0.095601,0.11007,0.16883,0.24879]},{"section":12,"text":"The patient's presentation of itchy papula-vesicular lesions and the DIF showing IgA deposits at the dermoepidermal junction and dermal papilla strongly suggest **bullous pemphigoid**.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.012059,0.021237,0.02632,0.031484,0.03685,0.044283,0.052827,0.068441,0.088767,0.1196,0.1829,0.31523],"unified_progress":[0.011845,0.020146,0.025388,0.032197,0.038564,0.051706,0.057027,0.078217,0.095999,0.11489,0.1772,0.29682]}],"deepseek-r1-distill-qwen-14b":[{"section":0,"text":"Okay, so I'm trying to figure out the diagnosis for this case.","dimension":7,"group":2,"is_degener