 the dermoepidermal junction makes me think of conditions like IgA-mediated diseases.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035631,0.060955,0.077689,0.089794,0.098877,0.10192,0.1049,0.10232,0.096074,0.088621,0.076859,0.066362],"unified_progress":[0.034645,0.064206,0.082564,0.094176,0.10042,0.10429,0.10267,0.098989,0.095331,0.088689,0.074809,0.05921]},{"section":6,"text":"One that comes to mind is IgA pemphigus.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025746,0.052298,0.068587,0.081349,0.094549,0.10138,0.11213,0.11391,0.10571,0.097582,0.080446,0.066318],"unified_progress":[0.026279,0.055362,0.078614,0.094167,0.10044,0.11637,0.10902,0.10547,0.098424,0.092059,0.071608,0.052178]},{"section":7,"text":"I recall that pemphigus is a group of autoimmune blistering diseases.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.019031,0.044002,0.060543,0.075675,0.093317,0.10339,0.11963,0.12407,0.11382,0.10064,0.081847,0.064026],"unified_progress":[0.021523,0.050527,0.076007,0.095866,0.10311,0.11579,0.11508,0.11002,0.10205,0.094036,0.068429,0.047556]},{"section":8,"text":"There are different types, like pemphigus vulgaris which involves IgG, but IgA pemphigus is less common.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.020338,0.042888,0.058944,0.074264,0.091585,0.10212,0.11797,0.12318,0.11496,0.10151,0.085099,0.067132],"unified_progress":[0.022851,0.051325,0.075039,0.095295,0.10255,0.11261,0.11378,0.10996,0.10269,0.09528,0.069817,0.048805]},{"section":9,"text":"In IgA pemphigus, the antibodies target the desmogleins, which are proteins in the epidermis that help hold skin cells together.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03041,0.052202,0.067884,0.082228,0.094416,0.10142,0.1101,0.11024,0.10522,0.094056,0.082248,0.069582],"unified_progress":[0.033677,0.064206,0.083645,0.096966,0.10456,0.1065,0.10462,0.10112,0.098532,0.084992,0.068518,0.052668]},{"section":10,"text":"When IgA binds to these, it can cause the skin to blister.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040264,0.056247,0.071508,0.084152,0.094283,0.099652,0.10484,0.10465,0.10175,0.092455,0.081737,0.06846],"unified_progress":[0.038588,0.065611,0.083593,0.094849,0.10213,0.10546,0.10364,0.099092,0.096209,0.086653,0.070792,0.053376]},{"section":11,"text":"The lesions are often vesicular or bullous, which fits the papula-vesicular description here.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034476,0.062471,0.076633,0.086604,0.093853,0.096808,0.10216,0.1004,0.096831,0.088231,0.083916,0.077621],"unified_progress":[0.04164,0.072977,0.086179,0.095385,0.1006,0.10222,0.099139,0.096096,0.095117,0.082112,0.070004,0.058527]},{"section":12,"text":"Another possibility could be other IgA-related conditions, like IgA dermatitis or maybe even some forms of urticaria, but those usually don't have the same immunofluorescence pattern.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027545,0.048703,0.064628,0.0771,0.09045,0.098634,0.1083,0.11166,0.10918,0.1018,0.088845,0.073152],"unified_progress":[0.030883,0.05923,0.080788,0.092333,0.097867,0.11133,0.10518,0.10176,0.096736,0.09158,0.075123,0.057196]},{"section":13,"text":"Also, the chronic nature of the lesions for a year suggests it's not something acute like an allergic reaction.","dimension":5,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03346,0.051529,0.064453,0.075056,0.085847,0.093799,0.10211,0.10653,0.10827,0.10381,0.094917,0.080231],"unified_progress":[0.035818,0.059927,0.075156,0.085804,0.092987,0.098482,0.099911,0.10191,0.099521,0.097602,0.084418,0.06847]},{"section":14,"text":"I should also consider other autoimmune bullous diseases, but the IgA specificity points more towards IgA pemphigus.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024717,0.043478,0.06065,0.072306,0.086003,0.094391,0.10202,0.107,0.10785,0.10905,0.